{
  "name": "Chime of Disruption",
  "type": "equipment",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>This bone and gold bell chime is 6 inches in length and weighs about half a pound. The attuned can strike it as an <strong>action</strong> and expend a charge, causing a faint chiming sound within 60 feet of them (this is doubled to 120 feet if the attuned has proficiency with an <em>instrument </em>of any kind). Any creature that is concentrating that hears this sound finds it difficult to focus, and must make a concentration check. This check is done at disadvantage and the DC is 8 + 2 x your proficiency bonus. A deafened creature is unaffected by this chime.</p><p>Any creature that fails is concentration check as a result of this chime cannot concentrate on another spell until the end of their next turn.</p><table><thead><tr><td>Level</td><td>Save DC</td></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>1-4</td><td>12</td></tr><tr><td>5-8</td><td>14</td></tr><tr><td>9-12</td><td>16</td></tr><tr><td>13-16</td><td>18</td></tr><tr><td>17-20</td><td>20</td></tr></tbody></table><p><strong>Recharge:</strong> The Chime of Disruption regains all expended charges at Dawn.</p>",
      "chat": ""
    },
